   From September 30th to October 21st, Leonid Libkin (University of
   Edinburgh) will give a series of 7 courses related to his FSMP Chair on
   the topic of A modern theory of database query languages each Friday
   10:30-12:00 at IRIF, room 3052.
   SODA20

   25.9.2019
   Three papers coauthored by IRIF members will be presented at SODA’20,
   the main conference in algorithm design. Topics include the study of
   noisy models, aggregate rankings, and graph diameters.

   10.9.2019
   IRIF is seeking excellent candidates for about 10 postdoctoral
   positions in all areas of the Foundations of Computer Science. Deadline
   for applications: Nov. 3, 2019.

